<subSubSection id="BBC32FAAF936FF86FF40FDECD2C9FC0F" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F3667C21F936FF86FF40FDECD2C9FC0F" blockId="20.[151,1436,505,926]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="C1ADA033F936FF86FF40FDECD29BFDEF" bold="true" box="[199,498,613,638]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="34D907A2F936FF86FE7DFDECD19AFDEC" box="[506,755,613,638]" class="Reptilia" family="Polychrotidae" genus="Polychrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutirostris">
<emphasis id="C1ADA033F936FF86FE7DFDECD19AFDEC" box="[506,755,613,638]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Polychrus acutirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in a large part of the South 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FB54FDECD65DFDEF" box="[1235,1332,613,638]" name="United States of America" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">America</collectingCountry>
diagonal of open formations, in the Caatinga, Cerrado, Pantanal, and Chaco, with pointed records in the Amazonia and Atlantic Forest, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FE6FFD24D146FD57" box="[488,559,685,710]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FDB9FD24D1FAFD57" box="[574,659,685,710]" name="Bolivia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FD26FD27D063FD57" box="[673,778,686,710]" name="Paraguay" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FCCBFD24D0D2FD57" box="[844,955,685,710]" name="Argentina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="6BE260A4F936FF86FC49FD24D74AFD57" box="[974,1059,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1742,1764]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,215,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,215,1720]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distribution of examined material of Polychrus acutirostris and P. liogaster." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234993/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FB82FD27D74AFD57" box="[1029,1059,686,710]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FBDAFD24D7C8FD57" box="[1117,1185,685,710]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it is known from the states of Pará, Tocantins, Rondônia, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, Goiás, Maranhão, Piauí, Ceará, Paraíba, Pernambuco, Alagoas, Sergipe, Bahia, Minas Gerais, São Paulo, and in the Distrito Federal. In Amazonia it occurs in open vegetation enclaves in southern Rondônia and Pará, along the Tocantins River, in northern Mato Grosso, in 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FF10FCB4D3B7FCC7" box="[151,222,829,854]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and in northern 
<collectingCountry id="8BCE3CB1F936FF86FE1AFCB4D29AFCC7" box="[413,499,829,854]" name="Bolivia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="34D907A2F936FF86FE79FCB4D19EFCC4" box="[510,759,829,854]" class="Reptilia" family="Polychrotidae" genus="Polychrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutirostris">
<emphasis id="C1ADA033F936FF86FE79FCB4D19EFCC4" box="[510,759,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Polychrus acutirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is arboreal and diurnal, inhabits arboreal savannas, where it is found mainly on branches of trees and bushes (
<bibRefCitation id="974801D0F936FF86FD45FCE8D0ECFCEB" author="Avila-Pires" box="[706,901,865,890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">
Ávila-Pires 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FCCDFCE8D0ECFCEB" box="[842,901,865,890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Vitt 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FC44FCE8D097FCEB" box="[963,1022,865,890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1995.0">1995</number>
; Rodrigues 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FB03FCE8D7D6FCEB" box="[1156,1215,865,890]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1996.0">1996</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="974801D0F936FF86FB4CFCE8D3BAFC0F" author="Gainsbury" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Gainsbury, A. M. &amp; Colli, G. R. (2003) Lizard assemblages from natural cerrado enclaves in southwestern Amazonia: the role of stochastic extinctions and isolation. Biotropica, 35, 503 - 519. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7429.2003. tb 00607. x" type="journal article" year="2003">
Gainsbury &amp; Colli 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FF10FC0FD3BAFC0F" box="[151,211,902,926]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="974801D0F936FF86FF5AFC0CD2FCFC0F" author="Rodrigues" box="[221,405,901,926]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Rodrigues, M. T. (2003) Herpetofauna da Caatinga. In: Leal, I. R., Tabarelli, M. &amp; Silva, J. M. C. (Eds.), Ecologia e conservacao da Caatinga. Editora Universitaria, Universidade Federal de Pernambuco, Recife, pp. 181 - 236." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Rodrigues 
<number id="45116E06F936FF86FEDFFC0FD2FCFC0F" box="[344,405,902,926]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2003.0">2003</number>
